module

public import Mathlib
public import BrownianMotion.Gaussian.BrownianMotion

/-!
# Brownian Markov property at the ŌÉ-algebra level

Degenne's `BrownianMotion` package proves the weak Markov property in the
function-valued form: `IsPreBrownian.indepFun_shift` states that the shifted
increment map `ŌČ ‚Ü¶ (X (t‚āÄ + t) ŌČ ‚ąí X t‚āÄ ŌČ)_t` is independent (as a random
variable valued in `‚ĄĚ‚Č•0 ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ`) of the past evaluation map
`ŌČ ‚Ü¶ (X t ŌČ)_{t ‚Č§ t‚āÄ}`, and `IsPreBrownian.shift` states the shifted process
is again a pre-Brownian motion.

The textbook statement (Saporito, Theorem 5.1.4) is the ŌÉ-algebra form: the
post-`t‚āÄ` increment process is independent of the **natural filtration**
`ūĚďēŠĶČ_{t‚āÄ} = ŌÉ(X_u : u ‚Č§ t‚āÄ)`. This file closes that gap: by
`Filtration.natural_eq_comap`, the natural ŌÉ-algebra at `t‚āÄ` *is* the comap of
the past evaluation map, so the function-valued independence upgrades to

  `Indep ŌÉ(shifted increments) (Filtration.natural X _ t‚āÄ) P`,

which together with `IsPreBrownian.shift` is the full textbook package: after
`t‚āÄ`, Brownian motion **restarts afresh, independently of its entire past**.

## Main results

* `shift_indep_natural` ‚ÄĒ ŌÉ(increments after `t‚āÄ`) is independent of the
  natural filtration at `t‚āÄ`.
* `brownian_markov_property` ‚ÄĒ the textbook package: the shifted increment
  process is a pre-Brownian motion *and* independent of `ūĚďēŠĶČ_{t‚āÄ}`.
-/

@[expose] public section

namespace MathFin

open MeasureTheory ProbabilityTheory
open scoped NNReal ENNReal

variable {ő© : Type*} {mő© : MeasurableSpace ő©} {P : Measure ő©}
  {X : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0 ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ}

/-- **ŌÉ-algebra form of the weak Markov property.** The ŌÉ-algebra generated by
the shifted increment map `ŌČ ‚Ü¶ (X (t‚āÄ + t) ŌČ ‚ąí X t‚āÄ ŌČ)_t` is independent of
the natural filtration `ŌÉ(X_u : u ‚Č§ t‚āÄ)`. Upgrade of Degenne's
`IsPreBrownian.indepFun_shift` via `Filtration.natural_eq_comap`. -/
theorem shift_indep_natural [h : IsPreBrownian X P]
    (hX : ‚ąÄ t, Measurable (X t)) (t‚āÄ : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0) :
    Indep
      (MeasurableSpace.comap (fun ŌČ (t : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0) ‚Ü¶ X (t‚āÄ + t) ŌČ - X t‚āÄ ŌČ) inferInstance)
      (Filtration.natural X (fun t ‚Ü¶ (hX t).stronglyMeasurable) t‚āÄ) P := by
  rw [Filtration.natural_eq_comap]
  exact (IndepFun_iff_Indep _ _ _).1 (h.indepFun_shift hX t‚āÄ)

/-- **Theorem 5.1.4 (Brownian Markov property).** For a pre-Brownian motion
`X` and any `t‚āÄ ‚Č• 0`, the post-`t‚āÄ` increment process
`t ‚Ü¶ X (t‚āÄ + t) ‚ąí X t‚āÄ` is itself a pre-Brownian motion, and it is
independent of the natural filtration `ūĚďēŠĶČ_{t‚āÄ} = ŌÉ(X_u : u ‚Č§ t‚āÄ)` ‚ÄĒ the
ŌÉ-algebra of the *entire* past, not merely finitely many past evaluations. -/
theorem brownian_markov_property [h : IsPreBrownian X P]
    (hX : ‚ąÄ t, Measurable (X t)) (t‚āÄ : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0) :
    IsPreBrownian (fun t ŌČ ‚Ü¶ X (t‚āÄ + t) ŌČ - X t‚āÄ ŌČ) P ‚ąß
    Indep
      (MeasurableSpace.comap (fun ŌČ (t : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0) ‚Ü¶ X (t‚āÄ + t) ŌČ - X t‚āÄ ŌČ) inferInstance)
      (Filtration.natural X (fun t ‚Ü¶ (hX t).stronglyMeasurable) t‚āÄ) P :=
  ‚ü®h.shift t‚āÄ, shift_indep_natural hX t‚āÄ‚ü©

end MathFin
